description: {"blocks":[{"key":"6rspi","text":"Ulcerative colitis and Crohn’s Disease are chronic inflammatory bowel diseases (IBD) of unknown cause characterized by a relapsing-remitting behavior. Growing evidence supports the idea that the epithelial barrier plays a central role in the pathogenesis of IBD as well as in its evolution over time, thus representing a potential target for novel therapeutic options. ","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"7eds9","text":"In the last decade, the introduction of 3D epithelial cultures from ex vivo-expanded intestinal adult stem cells (ASCs) has impacted our ability to study the function of the epithelium in several gastrointestinal disorders, including IBD.","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":68,"length":7}],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"d73ik","text":"Here, we describe in detail a reproducible protocol to generate Matrigel-embedded epithelial organoids from ASCs of non-IBD and IBD donors using small colonic biopsies, including steps for its optimization. A slightly modified version of this protocol is also provided in case surgical samples are used.","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"b9psu","text":"With this method, epithelial organoids can be expanded over several passages, thereby generating a large quantity of viable cells that can be used in multiple downstream analyses including genetic, transcriptional, proteomic and/or functional studies. In addition, 3D cultures generated using our protocol are suitable for the establishment of 2D cultures, which can model relevant cell-to-cell interactions that occur in IBD mucosa.","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"d83q6","text":"Wash 1-2 times with ≈ 10 mL DPBS at room temperature by gentle manual flipping for a few seconds to remove the antimicrobial cocktail.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":111,"length":22}],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"kp9b","text":"Incubate the biopsies with 10 mL of the crypt isolation buffer for 45 min at 4°C under gentle agitation on a platform rocker.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":40,"length":22}],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8j674","text":" Wash once with ≈ 10 mL cold DPBS by gentle manual flipping for a few seconds to remove the crypt isolation buffer.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":92,"length":23}],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2vm42","text":"To start collecting the fractions enriched with viable crypts, add 10 mL cold DPBS and shake vigorously by hand for 15-20 seconds. {"blocks":[{"key":"95gqc","text":"Repeat Steps 8-9 until no additional crypts are released. Usually, no crypts are collected after 5-6 shaking cycles.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":7,"length":9}],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2kpst","text":"Wash the surgical sample with ≈ 20 mL cold DPBS by gentle manual flipping for a few seconds. Discard the DPBS and repeat the washing until the DPBS becomes clear.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9mmhp","text":"Transfer the sample to a 10 cm Petri dish and remove the submucosa and larger contaminating blood vessels with scissors and scalpel.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"fhq0l","text":"Cut the sample into pieces of 0.2-0.3 cm2, transfer them to a new 50 mL Falcon tube and perform a couple of additional washes with ≈ 20 mL cold DPBS by gentle manual flipping for a few seconds.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sup","offset":40,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"1fcic","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"2athv","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":[]},{"key":"tr7h","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"IMMUTABLE","data":{"blocks":[{"data":[],"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"97plv","text":"Avoid processing more than 15-20 sample pieces in one 50 mL Falcon tube since it could compromise the efficiency of crypt release  and increase the risk of crypt culture contamination by microorganisms.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9rvuo","text":"Incubate the sample in 20 mL of the antimicrobial cocktail for 20 min at room temperature under gentle agitation on a platform rocker.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":36,"length":22}],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"2d47l","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"ee2b","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"asqpr","text":"Wash 1-2 times with ≈ 20 mL DPBS at room temperature to remove the antimicrobial cocktail.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":67,"length":22}],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4qrcu","text":"Incubate with 10 mM DTT for 8 min at room temperature under gentle agitation on a platform rocker to remove the mucus.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"9dhhe","text":"Wash 1-2 times with ≈ 20 mL cold DPBS to remove DTT.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"en4b3","text":"Incubate the sample pieces with 20 mL of crypt isolation buffer for 45 min at 4°C under gentle agitation on a platform rocker.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":41,"length":22}],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"aofai","text":"Remove the EDTA buffer and wash once with 20 mL cold DPBS by gentle flipping.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"a9bo","text":"Resuspend the sample pieces in 20 mL cold DPBS and perform 1-2 manual vigorous shakes for 10-15 seconds each to remove the mucus, debris and dead cells. {"blocks":[{"key":"afqld","text":"Spin the crypt fractions at 150 x g for 3 min at 4°C.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"d0n67","text":"Remove the organoid growth medium and wash the wells once with ≈ 250 µL cold DPBS per well.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":11,"length":22}],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4bn7q","text":"Add 1 mL cold Recovery solution for every ≈ 3 drops of 25 µL Matrigel. Scrape the drops from the well surface with the P1000 micropipette tip and collect them in ice-cold 15 mL Falcon tubes. Avoid excessive pipetting since the organoids can stick to the tip and tube walls. Fill one Falcon tube with approximately 20 Matrigel drops maximum.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"fcpff","text":"Incubate for 30-40 min on ice, gently inverting the tubes every 5-10 min to facilitate Matrigel depolymerization.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"80i5u","text":"During Step 42, prepare the organoid dissociation solution (without yet adding the dispase to prevent loss of enzymatic activity) and pre-warm it in a water bath at 37°C. Consider that 5 mL solution will be prepared per Falcon tube containing the organoids/Recovery solution mix.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":7,"length":7},{"style":"italic","offset":28,"length":30}],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4uu9b","text":"Fill each tube containing the Recovery solution and organoids with additional 5-7 mL cold WM and spin at 400 x g for 3 min at 4°C.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"dvpf3","text":"During the spin, add dispase to the organoid dissociation solution.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":36,"length":30}],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"f55mo","text":"Discard the supernatant with a 5 mL pipette first, and then with a P1000 micropipette to completely remove the solution. To resuspend the organoid pellet, first gently add 1 mL of the pre-warmed organoid dissociation solution, pipet gently 2-3 times, and then add the remaining 4 mL.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":195,"length":30}],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"30d1q","text":"Leave the Falcon tubes in the cell incubator or in a water bath at 37°C for 15-20 min gently inverting the tubes every 5-10 min.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"dqcrp","text":"Mechanically dissociate the organoids with a G20-G21 needle mounted on a 5 mL syringe. It will take 2-5 min per tube, depending on weather the culture is derived from crypts or from a previously expanded organoid culture. Avoid generating too many bubbles in the solution while syringing.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"93mer","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":[]},{"key":"v6mt","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"IMMUTABLE","data":{"blocks":[{"data":[],"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"7cgg4","text":"Organoid dissociation usually takes longer if performed on a previously expanded organoid culture than on a crypt culture. In either case, if big clusters are still present, repeat the syringing until no cell aggregates are visible in the suspension. The extent of organoid dissociation can also be monitored by microscope observation.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"efbvk","text":"Spin dissociated organoids at 600-800 x g for 4 min at 4°C.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"f1a6s","text":"Discard the supernatant with a 5 mL pipette first, and then with a P1000 micropipette to completely remove the solution.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"491mh","text":"Perform 3 additional washes with ≈ 5 mL cold washing medium at 600-800 x g for 4 min at 4°C to completely remove the dispase. Perform the first two washes in the 15 mL Falcon tube and the last wash in a 1.5 mL Eppendorf tube if the required final volume of Matrigel fits in. At this point single cells from dissociated organoids can be cryopreserved (Step 51.1) or used for the generation of 2D cultures (Step 51.2).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":45,"length":14},{"style":"bold","offset":351,"length":9},{"style":"bold","offset":405,"length":9}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"7c258","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4fg2f","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"bib1o","text":"For cryopreservation, perform the following:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4h3bg","text":"- Transfer a volume of single cells corresponding to 4-6 original Matrigel drops to a new cold cryopreservation tube.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4dmif","text":"- Spin at 600-800 x g for 4 min at 4°C.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1d3p8","text":"- Resuspend the cell pellet in 1 mL ice-cold Freezing Medium and transfer the sample to a freezing container.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"5323i","text":"- Store the sample at -80°C for 24h and transfer to a liquid nitrogen container for long-term storage.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"80knj","text":"- To thaw, resuspend the cell-containing cryopreservation tube in 5-10 mL warm washing medium.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":79,"length":15}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"f6b8g","text":"- Spin at 700 x g for 4 min at 4°C, resuspend in 1 mL cold washing medium and transfer to a new cold Eppendorf tube.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":59,"length":14}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"cgc0p","text":"- Spin again at 700 x g for 4 min at 4°C.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"hu4e","text":"- At this point, go to  Step 52. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":24,"length":7}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"f4adu","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"5tuit","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"IMMUTABLE","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"24gqg","text":"For cryopreserved cultures, the suggested seeding dilution after thawing is lower than the one used for passaging fresh cultures. We usually work with a dilution ratio of 1:2-1:3.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"crb84","text":"Resuspend the cell pellet in Matrigel supplemented with 10 µM Y-27632. The volume of Matrigel must be adjusted to the total number of drops (22-25µL Matrigel/drop) that will be seeded. Avoid bubbles while resuspending.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"d85lp","text":"Seed the required Matrigel drops in the pre-warmed 48-well plate and put the plate back in the incubator for 15-20 min to allow the Matrigel to solidify.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9p5ad","text":"Overlay each Matrigel-embedded dome with 250 µL of organoid growth medium supplemented with 10 µM Y-27632.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":51,"length":22}],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"bbnaj","text":"Change the medium with fresh organoid growth medium (without Y-27632) every 48-72h hours. Organoid cultures grown for 5-6 days are typically ready to be used for differentiation (Steps 56-59) or for further expansion by repeating the procedure described in this section (Steps 38-55).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":29,"length":22},{"style":"bold","offset":179,"length":11},{"style":"bold","offset":271,"length":11}],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"6tbdj","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"70i6j","text":"  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":[]},{"key":"bskrk","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"6d7fk","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"image","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"guid":"E7878B40AAC211EC8C7A85EAE1BD487D","height":408,"id":310276,"is_video":false,"legend":{"blocks":[{"data":[],"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"8qpbv","text":"Stem-cell enriched organoid culture 5 days after passaging. Crypts have been obtained from the not inflamed sigmoid mucosa of a UC patient.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":[]},"mime":"image/jpeg","nestedSelector":null,"original_name":"168STEM1C.jpg","placeholder":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/jragbn5uf.jpg","shadow":false,"source":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/jraebn5uf.jpg","webp_placeholder":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/jrafbn5uf.webp","webp_source":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/jradbn5uf.webp","width":550}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"v9qd","text":"Carefully aspirate the organoid growth medium from the culture generated in the previous section. Avoid detaching the Matrigel drops from the bottom of the wells.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":23,"length":22}],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9qc0b","text":"Perform two washes of ≈ 250 µL/well for 10 min each with warm basic medium to remove the culture components by diffusion through the Matrigel dome. Meantime, prepare the organoid differentiation medium.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":62,"length":12},{"style":"italic","offset":170,"length":31}],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"cf4se","text":"Add 250 µL of the organoid differentiation medium to each well.
